    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <description><![CDATA[Free/Libre Open Source Software binaries of [VS Code](https://community.chocolatey.org/packages/vscode).

VSCodium is a community-driven, freely-licensed binary distribution of Microsoft's editor VS Code.

![screenshot](https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/Thilas/chocolatey-packages@c6bc7188363aecd38726935a305d586a594b0525/vscodium/screenshot.png)

VS Code is a lightweight but powerful source code editor which runs on your desktop and is available for Windows, macOS and Linux. It comes with built-in support for JavaScript, TypeScript and Node.js and has a rich ecosystem of extensions for other languages (such as C++, C#, Java, Python, PHP, Go) and runtimes (such as .NET and Unity).

## Features

* **Meet IntelliSense:** Go beyond syntax highlighting and autocomplete with IntelliSense, which provides smart completions based on variable types, function definitions, and imported modules.
* **Print statement debugging is a thing of the past:** Debug code right from the editor. Launch or attach to your running apps and debug with break points, call stacks, and an interactive console.
* **Git commands built-in:** Working with Git and other SCM providers has never been easier. Review diffs, stage files, and make commits right from the editor. Push and pull from any hosted SCM service.
* **Extensible and customizable:** Want even more features? Install extensions to add new languages, themes, debuggers, and to connect to additional services. Extensions run in separate processes, ensuring they won't slow down your editor. [Learn more about extensions.](https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/extension-gallery)
]]></description>
    <summary>VSCodium (Portable)</summary>
    <releaseNotes><![CDATA[[Releases](https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/releases)

update vscode to [1.116.0](https://code.visualstudio.com/updates/v1_116)

## What's Changed
* build: bump Node version pins for loong64 and riscv64 by @CSharperMantle in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2760
* docs: fix typo 'anouncements' → 'announcements' in telemetry.md by @bhaskarvilles in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2721
* Add/docs windows build commands by @bhaskarvilles in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2722
* docs: add Windows troubleshooting section (GPO, context menu, Defender) by @bhaskarvilles in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2723
* Clarify incompatibility by @Chealer in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2601
* build(deps): bump picomatch in /font-size by @dependabot[bot] in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2763
* feat: update electron to 39.8.4 by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2764
* Fix DEB issue with PowerPC64 Little Endian by @lex-ibm in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2766
* Enable RPMs, DEBs, and CLI for PowerPC64 Little Endian by @lex-ibm in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2767
* Enable PowerPC64 Little Endian to build with Electron 41.y.z by @lex-ibm in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2771
* build(deps-dev): bump lodash-es from 4.17.23 to 4.18.1 in /font-size by @dependabot[bot] in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2773
* build(deps-dev): bump lodash from 4.17.23 to 4.18.1 in /font-size by @dependabot[bot] in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2774
* fix(ppc64): update sysroot checksum by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2775
* refactor: split some scripts by os by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2776
* Fix issue with RPMs and DEBs when packaging for PowerPC64 LE by @lex-ibm in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2778
* Use vscode sysroot prefix -glibc-2.28 for ppc64le by @lex-ibm in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2785
* fix(update): update isLatestVersion() to compare versions by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2777
* ci: improve workflows by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2795
* feat(1.116): update patches by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2796
* build(deps): bump zizmorcore/zizmor-action from 0.5.2 to 0.5.3 by @dependabot[bot] in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2798
* refactor: patches by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2797
* feat: add cooldown setting to update by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2799
* docs: replace old url with archived one by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2800
* enable having space-separated args for terminal.external.linuxExec by @timkenhan in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2790
* build(font-size): update and lock dependencies by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2803
* build(win32): appx contextmenu by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2801
* feat: disable onboarding screen by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2804
* ci: update actions by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2805
* fix: disable wip appx by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2807
* feat(1.116): update apis by @daiyam in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2808

## New Contributors
* @CSharperMantle made their first contribution in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2760
* @bhaskarvilles made their first contribution in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2721
* @Chealer made their first contribution in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2601
* @timkenhan made their first contribution in https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/pull/2790

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium/compare/1.112.01907...1.116.02821

